EJIKEME OMENAZU Barrister Adebayo Ibrahim Razak, the DPGLAGOS Lagos East Senatorial Coordinator, has been appointed as the Public Relations Officer (PRO) of the directorate. According to a statement issued by Bishop Dr. Theophilus Taiwo Ajose, the Lagos DPG Director, all DPGLAGOS Coordinators and officers were urged not to make public statements or granting interviews or release messages or posts to the print, electronic or social media on behalf of the directorate. Ajose said: “All public releases and information shall henceforth be handled by the office of the State Director or the Public Relations Officer. Any violation of this directive shall not be taken lightly. Ajose, in a statement made available to Sunday INDEPENDENT, expressed his appreciation all church fathers and leaders for their “invaluable contribution, support, encouragement, involvement, sacrifices and commitment to the cause of the prophetic political destiny of the church and the practical political alignment and integration into the mainstream political narratives of our dear State of Excellence and nation. “Our achievements so far at DPG LAGOS from the grassroots upward and our massive numerical structures of people and membership demand that we must be proactive while being gentle as dove, wise as serpent and as lambs among the wolves.”